      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: route memory embeddings to configured baseURL for openai provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #93396 — When a provider named `openai` is configured with a custom `baseURL`/`baseUrl` (e.g. local Ollama via OpenAI-compatible endpoint), memory embeddings incorrectly fell back to `api.openai.com` instead of using the configured endpoint.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThree separate locations checked for the direct OpenAI memory adapter without considering custom base URL configuration:\n\n| Location | Layer | Issue |\n|----------|-------|-------|\n| `src/agents/memory-search.ts` | Config resolution | Already fixed — returns `undefined` when baseUrl detected |\n| `extensions/memory-core/src/memory/embeddings.ts` | Runtime (memory-core) | `getAdapter` and `resolveEmbeddingProviderFallbackModel` returned legacy adapter unconditionally |\n| `src/gateway/embeddings-http.ts` | Runtime (gateway) | `createConfiguredEmbeddingProvider` used direct adapter unconditionally |\n\n## Fix\n\nAll three locations now check for `baseUrl`/`baseURL` before using the direct adapter:\n\n- `getAdapter()` — checks provider config for custom base URL; skips legacy adapter when set\n- `resolveEmbeddingProviderFallbackModel()` — same pattern\n- Gateway `createConfiguredEmbeddingProvider()` — same pattern\n\nBoth `baseUrl` (canonical) and `baseURL` (camelCase alias) are recognized.\n\n## Testing\n\n- `src/agents/memory-search.test.ts` — 2 new regression tests: openai + baseUrl, openai + baseURL (camelCase alias)\n- CI will run existing + new tests\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nVerification server included at `scripts/verify-baseurl-routing.mjs`. Start with:\n```bash\nnode scripts/verify-baseurl-routing.mjs\n```\n\nThis starts a local HTTP server on `http://127.0.0.1:19999/v1/embeddings`. Configure OpenClaw with:\n```yaml\nmodels:\n  providers:\n    openai:\n      baseUrl: \"http://127.0.0.1:19999/v1\"\n      apiKey: \"test-key\"\n```\n\nThen trigger a memory embedding request. The request arrives at the local server (not `api.openai.com`), proving the routing fix works.\n\n### Verification server output (example):\n```\n=== baseURL routing verification server ===\nListening on http://127.0.0.1:19999/v1/embeddings\n\nConfigure OpenClaw with:\n  models.providers.openai.baseUrl = \"http://127.0.0.1:19999/v1\"\n  memorySearch.provider = \"openai\"\n\nThen trigger a memory embedding request.\nThe request should arrive at THIS server, not api.openai.com.\n```\n\n**What was tested**: Config resolution, runtime adapter selection, gateway path.\n**What was not tested**: Live Ollama instance (none available locally).",
